    ],
    "syverson_one_paragraph": "Free-goods and digital-mismeasurement explanations cannot account for the post-2004 productivity slowdown because (i) the slowdown was global with no correlation to ICT intensity, (ii) consumer-surplus estimates are an order of magnitude too small, (iii) IT-industry productivity would have to be implausibly high if the story were true, and (iv) the GDP/GDI gap reflects profits, not labor income."
